Police officers in Trans Nzoia on Tuesday night recovered a cache of eight guns and 197 rounds of ammunition from a police officer attached to the Judiciary. According to a police report obtained by Citizen Digital, detectives were tipped off that an unidentified individual had been seen inside the home of a police officer who was not present. The officers who responded to the tip-off went to the aforementioned home, where an unidentified suspect fled, leaving the door open. When the officers went inside, they discovered that the house was leased to a police driver named Maxwell Tally Mutonyi, who lives in the Police Band quarters in the South B Nairobi Area. The officers discovered a cache of weapons in the living room, including one UZI SMG rifle with magazine, a Smith and Wesson revolver, six Germany Walther pistols with magazines and and 197 rounds calibre 9 mm ammunition. They also recovered one smoke trouser, a jungle pullover, an Angola jungle shirt, one modified swagger cane and a colorless liquid in a five litre jerrycan. Also Read: Outside the house was a blue Peugeot of registration No. KAC 001W which was also impounded. Probe into the matter is underway. Video Of The Day: CAS Rachel Shebesh and athlete Asbel Kiprop share their mental health journeys